comment: This is a page from a classical Chinese dictionary or lexicon, likely the *Shuowen Jiezi* or a similar work, featuring entries for characters related to "車" (vehicle/wheel). The layout includes small seal script (篆书) forms of the characters on the left, followed by their explanations in regular script (楷书), including definitions, phonetic annotations (切), etymological components (从...), and references to ancient texts. The right margin contains page numbers and section identifiers such as "小四百廿六" (small 426), "言五二一", "一印", and "魏三".
